00:39:07.089 --> 00:39:11.770
Let's take a brief look at what computers
look like today.

00:39:11.770 --> 00:39:17.049
Just to spend your time on the Web within
a browser, you have to deal with all the legacy

00:39:17.049 --> 00:39:22.339
decisions which have been made in the last
20 to 30 years in operating systems. Every

00:39:22.339 --> 00:39:26.839
time you boot up the computer, some computers
even check to see whether there's a floppy

00:39:26.839 --> 00:39:32.410
drive. It takes a long time to boot into your
computer. Once you're inside, you have to

00:39:32.410 --> 00:39:38.200
make sure you manage your applications. Every
one of your applications need to be up to

00:39:38.200 --> 00:39:43.250
date. You have to run antivirus software.
You have to back up your data. If you move

00:39:43.250 --> 00:39:47.819
across machines or if you try to upgrade your
PC, good luck with that. It takes an entire

00:39:47.819 --> 00:39:51.819
weekend to do so.
The experience is really, really complicated.

00:39:51.819 --> 00:39:58.819
So we wanted to rethink the entire experience
and distill it down to nothing but the Web.

00:39:59.150 --> 00:40:04.599
And that's what Chrome OS is.
Chrome OS can be applied to a variety of form

00:40:04.599 --> 00:40:09.970
factors. It is just an end-to-end computing
experience, a software experience. It can

00:40:09.970 --> 00:40:15.089
be applied to a variety of form factors. We
have chosen to focus initially on notebooks,

00:40:15.089 --> 00:40:19.170
because that's where most of the Web usage
is there today. That's where people use the

00:40:19.170 --> 00:40:24.380
Web the most. So we wanted to bring the Chrome
OS experience to notebooks.

00:40:24.380 --> 00:40:29.119
When you do that, when you run Chrome OS on
notebooks, you end up with a very different,

00:40:29.119 --> 00:40:36.119
unique experience. We call those Chromebooks.
So what makes Chromebooks different from other

00:40:36.220 --> 00:40:43.109
notebooks? Here are a few attributes. Every
Chromebook is instant to turn on. In fact,

00:40:43.109 --> 00:40:48.339
when you first get your device, when you unwrap
the box, you will be up and running within

00:40:48.339 --> 00:40:51.789
three minutes.
If you're one of the 160 million active users

00:40:51.789 --> 00:40:58.299
of Chrome, all your stuff is automatically
there with Chrome sync. Every time you boot

00:40:58.299 --> 00:41:05.190
up, you are up and running within eight seconds.
And each time you open the lid, before you

00:41:05.190 --> 00:41:10.520
can move your fingers and type on the keyboard,
you're connected within the Web.

00:41:10.520 --> 00:41:16.609
We have provided built-in connectivity options,
so wherever you use them, with connectivity

00:41:16.609 --> 00:41:23.500
options, you have data services which are
pay as you go, no contracts, no commitments.

00:41:23.500 --> 00:41:28.630
You get free monthly usage per month, and
you can buy day passes, et cetera. So you

00:41:28.630 --> 00:41:33.369
can be always connected.
They have all-day battery life. So I think

00:41:33.369 --> 00:41:37.079
this is really game-changing in terms of how
you think about your notebooks. I never carry

00:41:37.079 --> 00:41:42.430
power chargers around when I'm using a Chromebook.
It lasts all day, as long as you can charge

00:41:42.430 --> 00:41:47.319
it at home or at the hotel at the night, you're
all set. These are some of the attributes

00:41:47.319 --> 00:41:52.280
which make phones and tablets great as well.
But for the first time, we are bringing those

00:41:52.280 --> 00:41:56.490
wonderful attributes of mobile computing to
the world of notebooks.

00:41:56.490 --> 00:42:03.200
The software experience is very unique as
well. Because it is nothing but the Web, you

00:42:03.200 --> 00:42:09.369
can access your stuff anytime, anywhere. You
can ask multiple Chromebooks, you can share

00:42:09.369 --> 00:42:13.619
Chromebooks with people. Each time when you
open them, you get the latest and the greatest

00:42:13.619 --> 00:42:16.480
version of the Web application which you're
using.

00:42:16.480 --> 00:42:21.839
It gets better over time. I think this is
a concept people aren't used to on their computers.

00:42:21.839 --> 00:42:28.000
When you buy a PC, it's great on the first
day. But as you install applications, it slowly

00:42:28.000 --> 00:42:33.740
starts degrading over time. Because we update
Chromebooks automatically, we'll update them

00:42:33.740 --> 00:42:37.549
every few weeks, we actually think we can
make it better over time.

00:42:37.549 --> 00:42:42.119
To give you an example, as we have made all
the JavaScript speed improvements, your Chromebooks

00:42:42.119 --> 00:42:46.829
will get faster. With all the GPU acceleration
improvements we talked about, you will notice

00:42:46.829 --> 00:42:52.260
in a few months your Chromebooks are even
faster. And finally, security is built in

00:42:52.260 --> 00:42:56.319
from the ground up.
Every piece of user data on Chromebooks, by

00:42:56.319 --> 00:43:01.109
default, is encrypted.
Every time you boot up your computer, we take

00:43:01.109 --> 00:43:04.990
you through a verified boot sequence to make
sure you're secure.

00:43:04.990 --> 00:43:10.980
And, finally, you're within the Chrome sandbox.
Chrome sandbox, which is built into sandbox

00:43:10.980 --> 00:43:15.140
Web pages and plug-ins. We think it's a pretty
unique experience.

